# 📡 Neural DX Watcher — v10.1

**DX Cluster Dashboard & Advanced Radio Analysis Engine**

A local web application for DX monitoring and radio analysis, designed for the demanding amateur radio operator.  
Built to **observe**, **understand** and **step back** — not to generate visual noise.

---

## 🧭 Overview

**Neural DX Watcher** is a local web application that:

- connects to one or more **DX Clusters (Telnet)**
- displays **real-time spots** (HF / VHF / UHF)
- integrates **solar indices** (SFI, A, Kp…)
- maintains a **usable memory** of activity
- offers **multiple reading levels**, from live monitoring to strategic analysis
- **predicts** probable openings based on your activity and missing DXCCs

> The goal is not to see a lot,  
> but to **see clearly**.

---

## 🖥️ Main Pages

### 1️⃣ **Index** Page — Real-time & Operator Tracking

Displays the live spot stream, active bands, wanted DX, solar indices, and activity surge alerts.  
👉 **Goal: know what's happening right now.**

---

### 📡 **WATCHLIST · Tracking** Panel

> *"I wasn't at my desk — what did I miss?"*

Based on the watchlist, uses in-memory history, shows the latest spots per callsign.  
✅ A catch-up tool designed for the human operator.

---

### 2️⃣ **Map** Page — Observation Map

Classic map of individual spots — each point = one station.  
👉 **Goal: see where it's happening.** The Map page is an **execution tool**.

---

### 3️⃣ **Analysis** Page — Deferred META ANALYSIS

A deliberately non-real-time tool, based on application log analysis.  
👉 **A tool for stepping back**, not a gimmick.

---

### 4️⃣ **World** Page — Forecast & Anomalies

| Page | Nature | Question |
|---|---|---|
| Map | Raw observation | Who is active right now? |
| World | Interpreted analysis | Where is propagation abnormally favorable? |

Displays zones, not stations. Spatio-temporal clustering, noise filtering.  
👉 **World decides, Map executes.**

---

### 5️⃣ **Briefing**

Updated every 12 hours with essential DX information. Callsigns can be automatically added to the watchlist. You won't miss any expedition.

---

### 6️⃣ **Satellites**

Real-time tracking of amateur satellites (AO-91, RS-44, SO-50, ISS…). Local sgp4 computation, next passes (AOS/TCA/LOS), uplink/downlink frequencies from SatNOGS.

---

