## 🚀 Installation

```bash
git clone https://github.com/F1SMV/Neural-DX-Watcher.git
cd Neural-DX-Watcher
chmod +x start.sh
./start.sh
```

The application will be available at `http://localhost:8000`

---

## ⚙️ Technical Architecture

- Backend: Python / Flask
- Frontend: HTML / CSS / JavaScript
- Cluster: Telnet DX Cluster
- Analysis: dedicated Python scripts
- Storage: memory + local JSON files + **SQLite**

No cloud dependency.

---

## 🗂️ Version History

### v10.1 — COCKPIT Redesign · Radar Sweep · Improved Satellites · Bug Fixes

#### 🎛 COCKPIT Mode Visual Overhaul

**VHF PROPAGATION · VOACAP Panel**
- Simplified format: HTML table with 4 bands (50 / 70 / 144 / 432 MHz) × 6 time slots
- Color-coded cells by percentage (red → orange → yellow → green → blue)

**Radar Sweep Effect** (🆕 ON/OFF toggle button)
- Animated canvas beam via `requestAnimationFrame`, centered on the **operator's QTH**
- Concentric radar rings, fading trail, glowing QTH dot
- Pulsing spots synchronized to the beam — projected from real Leaflet coordinates
- `⬤ RADAR ON / ○ RADAR OFF` button in the Magic Band panel header
- State saved in localStorage

**Unified Activity Scale Legend** (🆕)
- 6 levels: CLOSED → WEAK → FAIR → OPENING → STRONG → HOT

**Cockpit Watchlist Tracking** (🆕)
- Watchlist panel cloned directly into cockpit column 3
- Shows the full watchlist sorted by last spot, no filter required
- Configurable purge selector (15 / 30 / 60 min)

**DX Spot Feed improvements**
- Calls displayed in **orange** (better readability), watchlist in yellow, new DXCC in red
- Distance shown **first** in the INFO column (no longer hidden by ellipsis)

**Page scrolling**
- Mouse wheel now scrolls the entire cockpit page freely (no more internal column scroll traps)

**Opening Strength gauge enlarged** — 132px → 200px

#### 🛰️ Satellites Page — Uplink/Downlink Frequencies

- Map popup enriched with **radio frequencies** for each satellite
- Source: SatNOGS API (`db.satnogs.org/api/transmitters/`), 6-hour server cache
- ↓ downlink in green · ↑ uplink in orange · mode (FM / Linear / CW…)
- Frequencies remain stable — preserved across position refreshes
- New backend route: `GET /api/satellites/frequencies/<norad_id>`

**Satellite type fix**
- Amateur satellites appeared as "unknown" in the Az/El table
- New `_infer_sat_type()` function: AO-, SO-, RS-, OSCAR, FUNCUBE, AMSAT → amateur; NOAA, METOP → weather; ISS, CSS → station
- Applied in both endpoints: positions and catalog

**Azimuth fix** 🔴 *(critical bug)*
- Azimuth readings were systematically off by **180°** (e.g. RS-44 showed 118° instead of 298°)
- Root cause: `atan2(-e, s)` instead of `atan2(e, s)` in the SEZ coordinate formula
- All azimuth calculations (current position, AOS/LOS passes) are now correct

---

### v10.0 — Predictive Engine · Sparklines · Push Alerts (optional)

#### 🔮 Personal Predictive Engine (`predictor.py`)

**SQLite collection** (`data/predictor.sqlite`): tables `spot_log`, `es_events`, `sessions`, `missing_dxcc`, auto-purge after 90 days.

**Probabilistic scoring**: seasonal/hourly Es patterns, directional boost, band factor, local history bonus, missing DXCC cross-reference with LoTW.

**Cockpit predictions panel**: TOP 5 most probable windows over the next 24 hours.  
Routes: `/api/predictions`, `/api/predictor/stats`, `POST /api/presence`

#### 📊 Sparklines in the DX Feed

40×14 px inline canvas · 6 bars of 10 minutes · auto-injected by MutationObserver

#### 🔔 Smart Push Alerts (`ntfy.sh`, optional)

3 types: watchlist spotted / NEW DXCC / 6m opening · 15-min SQLite cooldown · presence filter  
Routes: `/api/ntfy/status`, `POST /api/ntfy/test`

#### 🎨 Unified Design System

Glassmorphism, CRT scanlines, cyan palette applied across the entire application.

